<br>
Last night a SGA meeting of Guildleaders and one Officer were in attendance from the following, understanding that some could not make it.<br>
<br>
Amnesty:<br>
Cicotte<br>
Gharbard<br>
<br>
WotC:<br>
Carazar<br>
Nyse<br>
<br>
EoV:<br>
Nayl<br>
<br>
Iussu:<br>
Baratis<br>
<br>
We still need to hear from PoJ, Dragonchow, and AoD.<br>
<br>
The purpose of this meeting was to establish the following:<br>
Organization, Leadership, Raid Schedule &amp; Rules, SGA Direction, Raid Communications, and Temparary Freeze,<br>
<br>
Leadership &amp; Organization:<br>
<br>
During last nights meeting, it was determind that I would take command of the SGA. Each Guild of the SGA will provide the following to be involved in the SGA: Guild Leader, Assistant Guild Leader, and one officer for Raid cordinator. They will determine the direction in which the SGA will go from here on out, establishing policy and procedures for all SGA to follow. Thye will further set up the organization under the SGA banner adding to its structure as needed. These 21 members will make up what is called the SGA Elders.<br>
<br>
Temparary Freeze:<br>
<br>
As of this posting the SGA will be frozen with the seven Guilds that it currently has, this is only temparary as to allow the new leadership to define the direction and policies that the SGA will be formed under.<br>
<br>
Raids:<br>
<br>
Policy, Procedures, Communications, Schedule. these are topics that in the near future will be posted to this forum. most of these guide line are established, and at the discretion of the Raid Leader, Items as Need before greed will always apply in a SGA sanctioned raid. It will further be up to the Raid Leader as to weather the Raid is Open or Closed, depeding on its purpose. We will set a Raid schedule as each SGA Guild will plan a raid one per week, meaning that with seven guilds it will rotate every seven weeks for a SGA raid or event. These raids can be targeted for any level, lets not for get our lower levels. Also discussed was a alts night to.<br>
<br>
In raid communications we will enact the following policies:<br>
Raid Start Times will strictly be adhered to,<br>
Communications: All participating members of the SGA will be tagged with a reserved guild tag, if not tagged prioir to the start time of the raid you will be left behind.<br>
<br>
As soon as we can get a hold on the adminright to this forum we will have a public and private forums for guild events &amp; raids.<br>
<br>
I will post more as it come available.<br>
<br>
There will be a meeting for the SGA Guild leaders and Officers this Thursday October 4th 5pm pacific/6pm mountain/7pm central/8pm eastern/1am gmt<br>
<br>
Cicotte Wyndwalker/Stokei Sacredsabre<br>
Amnesty Guild Leader<br>
SGA <br>
<br>
PS There will be no flaming in this post if there is your respective Guild Leader will determine your fate, We are using this to work through on a civil level to enhance and strenghten the SGA. We need everyones support. All decisions from the SGA Elders are final.<br>
<br>
